Title: Variable declaration list comments from async functions are removed
Description: **TypeScript Version:**  2.2.1

**Code**

```typescript
async function example() {
    // result.value will be promise
    const promise = Promise.resolve("foo");
    await promise;

    // result.value will be "foo"
    return "foo";
}
```

**Expected behavior:**

Ignoring `__awaiter` and `__generator`, the output should include `// result.value will be promise`

**Actual behavior:**

```typescript
function example() {
    return __awaiter(this, void 0, void 0, function () {
        var promise;
        return __generator(this, function (_a) {
            switch (_a.label) {
                case 0:
                    promise = Promise.resolve("foo");
                    return [4 /*yield*/, promise];
                case 1:
                    _a.sent();
                    // result.value will be "foo"
                    return [2 /*return*/, "foo"];
            }
        });
    });
}
```

On further exploration, it looks like this is only happening when a comment appears before a variable declaration list.

```typescript
async function example() {
    // test abc
    let abc;

    // test def
    let def,
        // ghi
        ghi;

    // result.value will be promise
    const promise = Promise.resolve("foo");
    await promise;

    // result.value will be "foo"
    return "foo";
}
```

...becomes:

```javascript
function example() {
    return __awaiter(this, void 0, void 0, function () {
        var abc, def, 
        // ghi
        ghi, promise;
        return __generator(this, function (_a) {
            switch (_a.label) {
                case 0:
                    promise = Promise.resolve("foo");
                    return [4 /*yield*/, promise];
                case 1:
                    _a.sent();
                    // result.value will be "foo"
                    return [2 /*return*/, "foo"];
            }
        });
    });
}
```

Talk with @rbuckton this turned out to be harder problem than it looks... Couple thing we need to figure out

- Where should the comment go when there are two separate variable statement comment?
```ts
async function example() {
    // test abc
    let abc;

    // test def
    let def,
    ....
}
```

```js
function example() {
    return __awaiter(this, void 0, void 0, function () {
     --- what should this comment be -----
        var abc, def, 
    ....
}
```

- how we currently transform variable statement and hoist it declaration doesn't easily allow us to pass in information about the original variable statement (which we need to get the comment back)

> Where should the comment go when there are two separate variable statement comment?

Seems reasonable to separate variable declarations by comments the way they are now.

```typescript
async function example() {
    // test abc
    let abc;

    // test def, ghi
    let def, ghi;

    // test jkl
    let jkl,
        // test mno
        mno;
    ...
}
```

Output by default:
```typescript
function example() {
    return __awaiter(this, void 0, void 0, function () {
        // test abc
        var abc;
        // test def, ghi
        var def, ghi;
        // test jkl
        var jkl,
        // test mno
        mno;
        ...
}
```

Output with `--removeComments`:
```typescript
function example() {
    return __awaiter(this, void 0, void 0, function () {
        var abc, def, ghi, jkl, mno;
        ...
}
```
